According to Eric Werme USG <werme@zk3.dec.com>:
> BTW, given your hardware, 1963 KB/sec is not terribly exciting. V3
> should easily see that with a single disk.
Here, nfsv3-0.5.2 over stock 2.2.5 kernel; client is a Miata/516 MHz
(Alpha machine), server is Ultra5/333 with Solaris 7 (the Sun low-end
these days). 100baseT link.
Read performance is above 7 MB/s
Write performance is above 5 MB/s
NFSv3 is definetely better than NFSv2.
	--Thomas Pornin
